B.E2.80.94Punjab|PB]]-18\n| iso_code                = IN-PB\n| blank1_name_sec2        = \n| blank1_info_sec2        = \n| website                 = {{URL|gurdaspur.nic.in}}\n| footnotes               =\n}}\n'''Chandu Suja''' is a village in [[Batala]] in [[Gurdaspur district]] of [[Punjab, India|Punjab]] [[States and territories of India|State]], India. The village is [[Administration (government)|administrated]] by [[Sarpanch]] an elected representative of the village.\n\n== Demography ==\n{{as of|2011}}, The village has a total number of 161 houses and the population of 774 of which 399 are males while 375 are females according to the report [[published]] by [[Census India]] in 2011. The literacy rate of the village is 49.12%, lower than the state average of 75.84%. The population of children under the age of 6 years is 112 which is 14.47% of total population of the village, and child sex ratio is approximately 965 higher than the state average of 846.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.censusindia.gov.in/2011census/dchb/DCHB_Village_Release_0300.xlsx|title=DCHB Village Release|work=[[Census of India, 2011]]}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of villages in India]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Gurdaspur district}}\n\n{{coord|31|55|N|75|04|E|display=title|region:IN_type:city_source:GNS-enwiki}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Gurdaspur district]]\n\n\n{{Gurdaspur-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Chandu Suja\n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = \n| settlement_type         = Village\n| pushpin_map             = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = \n| coordinates             = \n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = [[India]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Punjab, India|Punjab]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of districts of India|Distr